(u,v) \mapsto \left(\frac{\sin u}{\cos v}, \frac{\sin v}{\cos u}\right)=\left(x, y\right)
T:= \{0\le u,v; u+v \le \frac {\pi}2\}
S:=\{0\le u,v \le 1\}
\begin{aligned} \frac {\sin u}{\cos v} &= \frac {\sin u'}{\cos v'} \\  \frac {\sin v}{\cos u} &= \frac {\sin v'}{\cos u'} \end{aligned}
\begin{aligned} \sin u\cos v' - \sin v'\cos u &= \sin u' \cos v - \sin v \cos u' \\ \sin(u-v')&=\sin(u'-v)\\ \Rightarrow u+v &=u'+v'\end{aligned}
